  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dcf\u0db4 \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dab \u0d94\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da2\u0db1\u0dca \u0da0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dcf \u0d92\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0db4\u0daf\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The Air Force is developing a thermo-humidification oxygen therapy unit",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The HEATED HUMIDIFIED OXYGEN THERAPY unit produced by the Sri Lanka Air Force to be used for the ease of breathing of patients with respiratory problems was officially handed over to President Gotabaya Rajapaksa yesterday (12) at the Presidential Office.",
        "According to the instructions of the President in the face of the Covid-19 epidemic, the equipment set has been created with the contribution of an expert medical team including Professor Ranil de Silva and Dr. Thilanka Ratnapala, according to the concept of Dr. Vidyajyothi, an international ambassador in the field of innovation.",
        "This device provides controlled temperature oxygen gas at high capacity with full humidity to patients with respiratory problems.",
        "Under the guidance of Air Force Commander Air Marshal Sudarshan Pathirana and under the supervision of Air Force Commanding Officer Group Captain Prasanna Martino, the Aircraft Maintenance Unit of the Air Force Engineer Corps carried out the production work.",
        "After checking the limits, safety features and performance standards, submitted to the National Drug Regulatory Authority of Sri Lanka, the electrical safety standards compliance has been confirmed by the University of Moratuwa.",
        "Although it is estimated that 15 lakhs will be spent on the production of the equipment, it is a special thing that the production work will be completed with a low amount of 03 lakhs.",
        "Currently, 50 sets of equipment are planned for production and production activities are carried out continuously according to the needs of health sectors."
      ],
